In article <Cu8oKL.722@trc.amoco.com>,
Scott T. Schad <zsts0c@trc.amoco.com> wrote:
>If all the countries of the world were capitalist democracies with the
>recognition of individual rights codified in their constitutions, national
>security would be a non-issue.

I doubt that.

>I choose not to sacrifice one
>iota of my country's security so a usenet group can have an "international"
>flavor.

Unfortunately for your argument, usenet is not confined to the US.  Neither
is the Internet.  You will have to arrange for a large network entirely
within the US before you can mandate against international flavors on it.

>I like secure borders and a high standard of living.

The second, possibly.  If you're serious about the first, you're living in
the wrong place.

